* If there are two threads accessing same object Thread1 is modifying the object and Thread2 is reading the object,
  as Thread2 is expecting original state of object, while Thread2 has modified the original object, this situation can create
  problem, to overcome this problem their concept called,
  
* Intrinsic Lock & Synchronization:
	- When Thread1 is accessing an object and you use Intrinsic Lock & Synchronization then it locks that object for that
	  perticular thread, therefore no any other thread can access the object at same time.  